@import 'mixins'

/* 
  Ð¡hoose one of two ways:
    1. manual method,
    2. using the fonts mixin;
1. Manual method (without the fonts mixin):
  Base Helvetica (example):
  @font-face {
    font-family: 'Helvetica-Base';
    src: url('/path/to/Helvetica/Base/Helvetica-Base.eot'); // IE9 Compat Modes
    src: url('/path/to/Helvetica/Base/Helvetica-Base.eot?#iefix') format('embedded-opentype'), // IE6-IE8
         url('/path/to/Helvetica/Base/Helvetica-Base.woff') format('woff'), // Pretty Modern Browsers
         url('/path/to/Helvetica/Base/Helvetica-Base.ttf')  format('truetype'), // Safari, Android, iOS
         url('/path/to/Helvetica/Base/Helvetica-Base.svg') format('svg'); // Legacy iOS
  }
2. Examples with the imported fonts mixin:
NOTE: do NOT use extensions (.woff, .svg etc) for path! Path must be '/path/to/OpenSans/opensans';
NOTE-2: required file formats are: `.woff, .woffs` (by default) OR alternatively `eot. .woff, .woffs, .svg, .ttf` if you use another mixin;
Base OpenSans:
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensans');
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensanslight', 300);
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensanssemibold', 600);
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensansbold', bold);
Italic OpenSans:
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensansItalic', 400, italic);
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensansLightItalic', 300, italic);
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensansSemiBoldItalic', 600, italic);
@include font-face('OpenSans', '/path/to/OpenSans/opensansBoldItalic', bold, italic); */
